qiptar - 1991-92 |url=http://www.zemrashqiptare.net/news/1278/kampionati-shqiptar-1991-92.html|date=14 October 2007|accessdate=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== Third round ==\n=== Quarterfinals ===\n{{OneLegStart}}\n{{OneLegResult|'''[[KS Sopoti Librazhd|Sopoti]]'''|| 3\u20130 |[[KS Burreli|Burrel Mat]] }}\n{{OneLegResult|'''[[KS Korabi Peshkopi|Korabi]]'''|| 2\u20130 |[[KS Bes\u00eblidhja Lezh\u00eb|Bes\u00eblidhja]] }}\n{{OneLegResult|'''[[KF Naft\u00ebtari|Naft\u00ebtari]]'''|| 3\u20132 |[[KS Luft\u00ebtari Gjirokast\u00ebr|Luft\u00ebtari]] }}\n{{OneLegResult|'''[[KS Pun\u00ebtori Patos|Pun\u00ebtori]]'''|| 3\u20130 |[[KS Butrinti Sarand\u00eb|Butrinti]] }}\n{{end}}\n\n=== Semifinals ===\n{{OneLegStart}}\n{{OneLegResult|'''[[KS Sopoti Librazhd|Sopoti]]'''|| 0\u20130, (3-2 pen) |[[KS Korabi Peshkopi|Korabi]]  }}\n{{OneLegResult|'''[[KS Pun\u00ebtori Patos|Pun\u00ebtori]]'''|| 1\u20130 |[[KF Naft\u00ebtari|Naft\u00ebtari]] }}\n{{end}}\n\n=== Final ===\n{{OneLegStart}}\n{{OneLegResult|'''[[KS Sopoti Librazhd|Sopoti]]'''|| 1\u20131, (3-2 pen) |[[KS Pun\u00ebtori Patos|Pun\u00ebtori]] }}\n{{end}}\n* [[KS Sopoti Librazhd|Sopoti]] and [[KS Pun\u00ebtori Patos|Pun\u00ebtori]] were promoted to [[1992\u201393 Albanian Superliga]].\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n* [http://www.zemrashqiptare.net/news/1277/kampionati-shqiptar-1991-92.html Giovanni Armillotta]\n* [http://www.calciomondialeweb.it/EUR/ALB/ALB2Div1992.htm Calcio Mondiale Web]\n\n{{Albanian First Division seasons}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1991\u201392 Albanian First Division}}\n[[Category:Albanian First Division seasons]]\n[[Category:1991\u201392 in Albanian football|2]]\n[[Category:1991\u201392 in European second tier association football leagues|Alba]]\n\n\n{{Albania-footy-competition-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition      = [[Albanian First Division]]\n| season           = 1991\u201392\n| winners          = [[KS Sopoti Librazhd|Sopoti]]\n| promoted         = {{ubl|[[KS Sopoti Librazhd|Sopoti]]|[[KS Pun\u00ebtori Patos|Pun\u00ebtori]]}}\n| relegated        = {{ubl|[[KF Memaliaj]]|[[KF Selenica]]}}\n| league topscorer = \n| biggest home win = \n| biggest away win = \n| highest scoring  = \n| matches          = \n| total goals      = \n| prevseason = [[1990\u201391 Albanian First Division|1990\u201391]]\n| nextseason = [[1992\u201393 Albanian First Division|1992\u201393]]\n}}\nThe '''1991\u201392 Albanian First Division''' (Albanian: ''Kategoria e Par\u00eb'') was the 45th season of a second-tier [[Association football]] league in [[Albania]].\n\nThe 2nd Division 1991/92, after the upheavals of 1991, takes on a new guise. The 24 participating teams are divided into two groups for the regular season, in which they only play the first round. In the second round, each group is split into four groups by geographical areas (North and South) with the teams retaining the points of the first phase: the winners of each group pass to the final knockout phase (from the quarterfinals to the final). [[KS Sopoti Librazhd|Sopoti Librazhd]] and [[KS Pun\u00ebtori Patos|Pun\u00ebtori Patos]] make it to the final, earning promotion to the 1st Division, with the first qualifying division champion on penalties. [[KF Memaliaj]] is relegated to the lower divisions, in which [[KF Selenica]] will also sink, which, relegated from the 1st Division, will not be accepted in the 2nd Division 1992/93. They will be replaced by two new clubs, the [[KF Amaro Divas|Amaro Divas Tirana]] and the [[KF Iliria|Iliria Fush\u00eb-Kruj\u00eb]].\n\n== First round ==\n=== Group A ===\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=PQ\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=BUR|name_BUR=[[KS Burreli|Burrel Mat]]\n|team2=SOP|name_SOP=[[KS Sopoti Librazhd|Sopoti]]\n|team3=BES|name_BES=[[KS Bes\u00eblidhja Lezh\u00eb|Bes\u00eblidhja]]\n|team4=KOR|name_KOR=[[KS Korabi Peshkopi|Korabi]]\n|team5=C\u00cbR|name_C\u00cbR=[[KS C\u00ebrriku|C\u00ebrriku]]\n|team6=SHK|name_SHK=[[KS Shkumbini Peqin|Shkumbini