lo-rio-bolsonaro-quase-quadruplicou-votos-em-relacao-a-2010.html|work=\u00daltimo Segundo|date=2014-10-06|accessdate=2019-08-22|language=pt-BR|first=iG S\u00e3o|last=Paulo}}</ref>\n| Elected<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tse.jus.br/eleicoes/eleicoes-anteriores/eleicoes-2010/candidaturas-votacao-e-resultados/estatisticas|title=Estat\u00edsticas das Elei\u00e7\u00f5es 2010|website=Tse.jus.br|accessdate=7 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2014 Brazilian general election|2014]]\n|[[Progressistas|PP]]\n| 464,572\n| 6.1\n| #1 <ref name=\"quadruplicou\" />\n| Elected<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.camara.leg.br/camaranoticias/noticias/POLITICA/475303-CONFIRA-A-APURACAO-DA-VOTACAO-POR-ESTADO.html|title=Confira a apura\u00e7\u00e3o da vota\u00e7\u00e3o por estado|website=2.camara.leg.br|accessdate=7 December 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{notelist}}\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q10304982|c=Category:Jair Bolsonaro|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|species=no|s=no|wikt=no}}\n* [http://www2.planalto.gov.br/ President of Brazil] {{in lang|pt}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.bolsonaro.com.br/}} {{in lang|pt}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Michel Temer]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title= [[President of Brazil]]|years=1 January 2019 \u2013 present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-prec}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-non|reason=First}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Brazilian order of precedence]]<br />1st in line<br />{{small|''as [[President of Brazil]]''}}}}\n{{s-fol|after=[[Hamilton Mour\u00e3o]]<br />{{small|''as [[Vice President of Brazil]]''}}}}\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Luciano Bivar]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Social Liberal Party (Brazil)|PSL]] nominee for [[President of Brazil]]|years=[[2018 Brazilian general election|2018]]}}\n{{s-inc|recent}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-new|party}}\n{{s-ttl|title= National President of [[Alliance for Brazil]]|years=21 November 2019 \u2013 present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Presidents of Brazil}}\n{{List of Current Heads of State of G20}}\n{{Current G20 Leaders}}\n{{BRICS}}\n{{Heads of State of the South America}}\n{{Portalbar|Biography|Brazil|Conservatism}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bolsonaro, Jair}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:21st-century Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Jair Bolsonaro| ]]\n[[Category:Bolsonaro family|Jair]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Venetian descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Calabrian descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of German descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian politicians]]\n[[Category:Presidents of Brazil]]\n[[Category:Brazilian anti-communists]]\n[[Category:Brazilian nationalists]]\n[[Category:Brazilian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Climate change denial]]\n[[Category:Critics of multiculturalism]]\n[[Category:Gun rights advocates]]\n[[Category:Conservatism in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Male critics of feminism]]\n[[Category:Members of the Chamber of Deputies (Brazil) from Rio de Janeiro (state)]]\n[[Category:People from Glic\u00e9rio]]\n[[Category:Right-wing populism in South America]]\n[[Category:Social Liberal Party (Brazil) politicians]]\n[[Category:Social Christian Party (Brazil) politicians]]\n[[Category:Progressive Party (Brazil) politicians]]\n[[Category:Stabbing survivors]]\n[[Category:Brazilian conspiracy theorists]]\n[[Category:Far-right politics in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Municipal Chamber of Rio de Janeiro councillors]]\n", "name_user": "Vcardozobr", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eForeign policy", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jair_Bolsonaro"}
{"title_page": "Jiong Qiu", "text_new": "{{Eastern name order|Qiu Jiong}}\n'''Jiong Qiu''' ({{lang|zh|\u90b1\u70af}}) is a Chinese-born American astrophysicist who won the [[Karen Harvey Prize]] for her work in solar flares.\n\n== Academic career ==\nQiu completed her Bachelors of Science in Astronomy in 1993 at [[Nanjing University]] located in [[Jiangsu]], China. Five years later she was awarded her PhD from the same university for her observational work in [[solar flares]]. Between acquiring her Bachelors and her PhD, between 1996\u20131997, she obtained a student fellowship that allowed her to work at [[Arcetri Observatory|Arcetri Astrophysics Observatory]] in Italy.\n\nFollowing her PhD, Qiu was accepted as a postdoc with the [[Big Bear Solar Observatory]] in California to further investigate solar flares, and to begin directly monitoring the Earth's atmosphere via measurements of [[Planetshine|Earthshine]].\n\nIn 2005, she began accepted a position with Montana State University, in Bozeman, Montana, as an assistant professor in Physics and Astronomy.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.physics.montana.edu/people/faculty/qui-jiong.html |publisher = Montana State University College of Letters and Sciences | title = Biographical Sketch}}</ref>\n\n== Scientific Work ==\nQiu has added contributed to the fields of [[Heliophysics]], Heliodynamics, and the [[Atmospheric sciences]]. She currently works with the Solar Physics Group at Montana State University. Her current research interests are:<ref>{{cite web | url = http://solar.physics.montana.edu/qiuj/ |publisher = Montana State University Solar Physics Division | title = Jiong Qiu}}</ref> \n* Magnetic Reconnection and Energy Release in Solar Flares\n* Large-scale solar magnetic reconfiguration \n* Small-scale Active Region Energy Release Events\n* Particle Acceleration in Flare Environment\n* Dynamics of Solar Flares and Active Regions\n* Earthshine Measurements of Global Atmospheric Change\n\nHer current research is centered on solar eruption events, and focused on understanding magnetic reconnection during these explosive events, using both ground-based telescopes and satellites.\n\n== Awards ==\nIn addition to receiving grants from the National Science Foundation and NASA, Qiu was the 2007 recipient of the [[Karen Harvey Prize]] for her major contributions to scientific understanding of the Sun, its effects on the atmosphere of the Earth, and its effects on Earth's climate.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://spd.aas.org/harvpc.html | publisher = American Astronomical Society Solar Physics Division | date = 9 June 2016 | author = J.B. Gurman | title = Previous Winners of the Karen Harvey Prize | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160526085152/http://spd.aas.org/harvpc.html | archive-date = 26 May 2016 | df =  }}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\n* {{cite journal |title = Chromospheric Evidence for Magnetic Reconnection |last1 = Falchi |first1 = A. |last2 = Qiu |first2 = J. |last3 = Cauzzi |first3 = G. |year = 1997 |journal = [[Astronomy and Astrophysics]] |volume= 328 |page = 371 |url = http://solar.physics.montana.edu/qiuj/publication/aa_chr.pdf |bibcode=1997A&A...328..371F}}\n* {{cite journal |title = Determining Heating Rates in Reconnection Formed Flare Loops of the M8.0 Flare on 2005 May 13 |last1 = Liu | first1 = W-J.|last2 = Qiu | first2 = J.| last3 = Longcope |first3 = D. W. |last4 = Caspi |first4 = A. | year = 2013 | journal = [[Astrophysical Journal]] | volume = 770 |issue=2 |page = 111 | url = http://solar.physics.montana.edu/qiuj/publication/apj_liu_2013.pdf |doi=10.1088/0004-637X/770/2/111|bibcode = 2013ApJ...770..111L |arxiv = 1304.4521 }}\n*{{cite journal | title = Magnetic Reconnection and Mass Acceleration in Flare-Coronal Mass Ejection Events | last1 = Qiu | first1 = J. |last2 = Wang |first2 = H. |last3 = Cheng |first3 = C.Z. |last4 = Gary |first4 = D.E. | year = 2004 |journal = [[Astrophysical Journal]] | volume = 604 | issue =  2| page = 900 | url = http://solar.physics.montana.edu/qiuj/publication/apj_acc.pdf| bibcode = 2004ApJ...604..900Q | doi = 10.1086/382122 }}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Qiu, Jiong}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nanjing University alumni]]\n[[Category:Women astronomers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Eastern name order|Qiu Jiong}}\n'''Jiong Qiu''' ({{lang|zh|\u90b1\u70af}}) is a Chinese-born American astrophysicist who won the [[Karen Harvey Prize]] for her work in solar flares.\n\n== Academic career ==\nQiu completed her Bachelors of Science in Astronomy in 1993 at [[Nanjing University]] located in [[Jiangsu]], China. Five years later she was awarded her PhD from the same university for her observational work in [[solar flares]]. Between acquiring her Bachelors and her PhD, between 1996-1997, she obtained a student fellowship that allowed her to work at [[Arcetri Observatory|Arcetri Astrophysics Observatory]] in Italy.\n\nFollowing her PhD, Qiu was accepted as a postdoc with the [[Big Bear Solar Observatory]] in California to further investigate solar flares, and to begin directly monitoring the Earth's atmosphere via measurements of [[Planetshine|Earthshine]].\n\nIn 2005, she began accepted a position with Montana State University, in Bozeman, Montana, as an assistant professor in Physics and Astronomy.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.physics.montana.edu/people/faculty/qui-jiong.html |publisher = Montana State University College of Letters and Sciences | title = Biographical Sketch}}</ref>\n\n== Scientific Work ==\nQiu has added contributed to the fields of [[Heliophysics]], Heliodynamics, and the [[Atmospheric sciences]]. She currently works with the Solar Physics Group at Montana State University. Her current research interests are:<ref>{{cite web | url = http://solar.physics.montana.edu/qiuj/ |publisher = Montana State University Solar Physics Division | title = Jiong Qiu}}</ref> \n* Magnetic Reconnection and Energy Release in Solar Flares\n* Large-scale solar magnetic reconfiguration \n* Small-scale Active Region Energy Release Events\n* Particle Acceleration in Flare Environment\n* Dynamics of Solar Flares and Active Regions\n* Earthshine Measurements of Global Atmospheric Change\n\nHer current research is centered on solar eruption events, and focused on understanding magnetic reconnection during these explosive events, using both ground-based telescopes and satellites.\n\n== Awards ==\nIn addition to receiving grants from the National Science Foundation and NASA, Qiu was the 2007 recipient of the [[Karen Harvey Prize]] for her major contributions to scientific understanding of the Sun, its effects on the atmosphere of the Earth, and its effects on Earth's climate.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://spd.aas.org/harvpc.html | publisher = American Astronomical Society Solar Physics Division | date = 9 June 2016 | author = J.B. Gurman | title = Previous Winners of the Karen Harvey Prize | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160526085152/http://spd.aas.org/harvpc.html | archive-date = 26 May 2016 | df =  }}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\n* {{cite journal |title = Chromospheric Evidence for Magnetic Reconnection |last1 = Falchi |first1 = A. |last2 = Qiu |first2 = J. |last3 = Cauzzi |first3 = G. |year = 1997 |journal = [[Astronomy and Astrophysics]] |volume= 328 |page = 371 |url = http://solar.physics.montana.edu/qiuj/publication/aa_chr.pdf |bibcode=1997A&A...328..371F}}\n* {{cite journal |title = Determining Heating Rates in Reconnection Formed Flare Loops of the M8.0 Flare on 2005 May 13 |last1 = Liu | first1 = W-J.|last2 = Qiu | first2 = J.| last3 = Longcope |first3 = D. W. |last4 = Caspi |first4 = A. | year = 2013 | journal = [[Astrophysical Journal]] | volume = 770 |issue=2 |page = 111 | url = http://solar.physics.montana.edu/qiuj/publication/apj_liu_2013.pdf |doi=10.1088/0004-637X/770/2/111|bibcode = 2013ApJ...770..111L |arxiv = 1304.4521 }}\n*{{cite journal | title = Magnetic Reconnection and Mass Acceleration in Flare-Coronal Mass Ejection Events | last1 = Qiu | first1 = J. |last2 = Wang |first2 = H. |last3 = Cheng |first3 = C.Z. |last4 = Gary |first4 = D.E. | year = 2004 |journal = [[Astrophysical Journal]] | volume = 604 | issue =  2| page = 900 | url = http://solar.physics.montana.edu/qiuj/publication/apj_acc.pdf| bibcode = 2004ApJ...604..900Q | doi = 10.1086/382122 }}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Qiu, Jiong}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nanjing University alumni]]\n[[Category:Women astronomers]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAcademic career:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 1996-1997 \u2192 1996\u20131997", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jiong_Qiu"}
{"title_page": "Derek Patmore", "text_new": "'''Derek Coventry Patmore''' (1908, [[London]] - 1972) was a British writer.  He was the great grandson of the poet [[Coventry Patmore]].\n\nPatmore was educated at [[Uppingham School]]. He worked as a war correspondent in the [[Balkans]] and the [[Middle East]], writing for the ''[[News Chronicle]]'' and the ''[[Daily Mail]]''.<ref>L. G. Pine, ed., ''The Author's and Writer's Who's Who'', 4th ed., 1960.</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''Selected Poems of Coventry Patmore'', London: Chatto and Windus, 1931.\n* ''Portrait of My Family'', London: Cassell, 1935.\n* ''I Decorate My Home'', London: Putnam, 1936.\n* ''Decoration for the Small Home'', London: Putnam, 1938.\n* ''Invitation to Roumania'', London: Macmillan, 1939.\n* ''French for Love'', London, 1940.\n* ''Balkan Correspondent'', New York: Harper, 1941.\n* ''Images of Greece'', London: Country Life, 1944.\n* ''Colour Schemes and Modern Furnishing'', London: The Studio, 1945.\n* ''Life and Times of Coventry Patmore'', Oxford University Press, 1949.\n* ''Italian Pageant'', London: Evans Bros, 1949.\n* ''A Traveller in Venice'', London: Methuen, 1951.\n* ''A Decorator's Notebook'', London: Falcon Press, 1952.\n* ''Dark Places of the Heart: A Novel'', London: Falcon Press, 1953.\n* ''Private History: An Autobiography'', 1960.\n* ''Canada'', London: Studio Vista, 1967.\n* ''D. H. Lawrence and the Dominant Male'', London: Covent Garden Press, 1970.\n* ''Homage to Marcel Proust'', London: Covent Garden Press, 1971.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Bruscello]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n* Mitchell, Owens, \"Room to Improve\", The New York Times, January 26, 2006\n\n== External Links ==\n\n* [https://rose.library.emory.edu/ Stuart A. Rose Manuscript, Archives, and Rare Book Library], Emory University: [http://pid.emory.edu/ark:/25593/8zr7f Derek Patmore papers, 1928-1968]\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Patmore, Derek}}\n[[Category:1908 births]]\n[[Category:English writers]]\n[[Category:1972 deaths]]\n\n\n{{UK-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Derek Coventry Patmore''' (1908, [[London]] - 1972) was a British writer.  He was the great grandson of the poet [[Coventry Patmore]].\n\nPatmore was educated at [[Uppingham School]]. He worked as a war correspondent in the [[Balkans]] and the [[Middle East]], writing for the ''[[News Chronicle]]'' and the ''[[Daily Mail]]''.<ref>L. G. Pine, ed., ''The Author's and Writer's Who's Who'', 4th ed., 1960.</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''Selected Poems of Coventry Patmore'', London: Chatto and Windus, 1931.\n* ''Portrait of My Family'', London: Cassell, 1935.\n* ''I Decorate My Home'', London: Putnam, 1936.\n* ''Decoration for the Small Home'', London: Putnam, 1938.\n* ''Invitation to Roumania'', London: Macmillan, 1939.\n* ''French for Love'', London, 1940.\n* ''Balkan Correspondent'', New York: Harper, 1941.\n* ''Images of Greece'', London: Country Life, 1944.\n* ''Colour Schemes and Modern Furnishing'', London: The Studio, 1945.\n* ''Life and Times of Coventry Patmore'', Oxford University Press, 1949.\n* ''Italian Pageant'', London: Evans Bros, 1949.\n* ''A Traveller in Venice'', London: Methuen, 1951.\n* ''A Decorator's Notebook'', London: Falcon Press, 1952.\n* ''Dark Places of the Heart: A Novel'', London: Falcon Press, 1953.\n* ''Private History: An Autobiography'', 1960.\n* ''Canada'', London: Studio Vista, 1967.\n* ''D. H. Lawrence and the Dominant Male'', London: Covent Garden Press, 1970.\n* ''Homage to Marcel Proust'', London: Covent Garden Press, 1971.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Bruscello]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n* Mitchell, Owens, \"Room to Improve\", The New York Times, January 26, 2006\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Patmore, Derek}}\n[[Category:1908 births]]\n[[Category:English writers]]\n[[Category:1972 deaths]]\n\n\n{{UK-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "A.C.Butner", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added external link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Derek_Patmore"}
